<div class="rounded-3 border p-3 shadow d-flex">
  <strong class="text-primary h3">RECALL</strong>
  <button class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-info mb-2" 
          data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#recall_modal">
    <i class="material-icons md-small">info</i>
  </button>

  <form id="recall" action="recall" method="GET" class="d-flex justify-content-end w-100 mb-2">
    <input type="hidden" value="" name="deckName">
    <input type="hidden" value="" name="deckType">
    <button id="recallButton" type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Start</button>
  </form>
</div>


<div id="recall_modal" class="modal fade">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
    
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h3 class="modal-title">RECALL</h3>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>All words will be displayed with images. Go over them until the class
          feels like they remember them fairly well. Then click START and a grid
          of cards will be shown face down below a search bar. Students call out 
          words and you type them into the search box. As you type, all words 
          that match will be highlighted. When there is only one, hit enter to 
          reveal the card. Continue untill all cards are revealed.</p>
        <p>You might also flip all cards that start with a certain letter. You
          can also flip a card by clicking on it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<script>
$(function(){
  $("#recallButton").on('click', (e)=>{
    e.preventDefault();
    if (!window.deckName) {
      alert("Please select a deck.");
    }
    else {
      $("#recall input[name='deckName']").val(window.deckName);
      $("#recall input[name='deckType']").val(window.deckType);
      $("#recall").submit();
    }
  });
});
</script>